	<text id="ruskin_to_mother_july_09_1867">
	    
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>1996L00311</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>           
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick</rs>,
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-07-09"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">9th July 1867</rs>
	                </date>
	                <day>Tuesday</day>
	                <salute>My dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs></salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	            </opener>
	            
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">The weather, though varying from windy and cold, to thundery and hot, allows me to get out nearly all day long, and I have no doubt that I gain more than I feel, - one cannot set a complete reaction of the system on foot in a week.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p2">    
	                <s id="s2">I met one of <rs key="5110922" type="person">Acland's</rs> friends a <rs key="19199837" type="person">Mr. Butler</rs>, the brother of the head master of <rs key="Q1247373" type="place">Harrow</rs>, on the lake yesterday: he was being rowed by the "Lord of the Isles," the gentlemen who lives in the house on the island: and they wanted me to go and see them in their Atlantic: I would not: but promised when I came back, which I really mean to do, to report myself at the island - it will on the whole <pb n="2"/> be more good than harm that I should know some of the people living here: and besides, I cannot help it but by mere savagery.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p3">     
	                <s id="s3">I have just got your long and quite legible letter of yesterday enclosing <rs key="95838041" type="person">Mr. Richmond's</rs>, very nice.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p4">     
	                <s id="s4">I will take care about lake air &amp;c in evening, but there is a sort of instinct in everybody in health, to get upon the water in the evening, which has been the same in all ages.</s>
	                <s id="s5">There is more marsh about these lakes than there ought to be however, and I will take care.</s>
	            </p>
	            
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever my dearest <rs key="47637407" type="person">Mother</rs>, Your most affectionate Son,</salute><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">J. Ruskin.</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	        </div>
	    </body>
	</text>      
	
